of%20not%20prosecuting%20a%20sitting%20president.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EJudge%20Tanya%20Chutkan%20agreed%20to%20the%20request%20by%20Special%20Counsel%20Jack%20Smith%20to%20dismiss%20the%20case%20against%20the%20president-elect%20%26quot%3Bwithout%20prejudice%2C%26quot%3B%20meaning%20it%20could%20potentially%20be%20revived%20after%20Trump%20leaves%20the%20White%20House%20four%20years%20from%20now.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BDismissal%20without%20prejudice%20is%20appropriate%20here%2C%26quot%3B%20Chutkan%20said%2C%20adding%20in%20the%20ruling%20that%20%26quot%3Bthe%20immunity%20afforded%20to%20a%20sitting%20President%20is%20temporary%2C%20expiring%20when%20they%20leave%20office.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETrump%2C%2078%2C%20was%20accused%20of%20conspiring%20to%20overturn%20the%20results%20of%20the%202020%20election%20he%20lost%20to%20Joe%20Biden%20and%20removing%20large%20quantities%20of%20top%20secret%20documents%20after%20leaving%20the%20White%20House%2C%20but%20the%20cases%20never%20came%20to%20trial.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESmith%20also%20moved%20on%20Monday%20to%20drop%20his%20appeal%20of%20the%20dismissal%20of%20the%20documents%20case%20filed%20against%20the%20former%20president%20in%20Florida.%20That%20case%20was%20tossed%20out%20earlier%20this%20year%20by%20a%20Trump-appointed%20judge%20on%20the%20grounds%20that%20Smith%20was%20unlawfully%20appointed.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20special%20counsel%20paused%20the%20election%20interference%20case%20and%20the%20documents%20case%20this%20month%20after%20Trump%20defeated%20Vice%20President%20Kamala%20Harris%20in%20the%20November%205%20presidential%20election.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESmith%20cited%20the%20long-standing%20Justice%20Department%20policy%20of%20not%20indicting%20or%20prosecuting%20a%20sitting%20president%20in%20his%20motions%20to%20have%20the%20cases%20dismissed.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20Government's%20position%20on%20the%20merits%20of%20the%20defendant's%20prosecution%20has%20not%20changed%2C%26quot%3B%20Smith%20said%20in%20the%20filing%20with%20Chutkan.%20%26quot%3BBut%20the%20circumstances%20have.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt%20has%20long%20been%20the%20position%20of%20the%20Department%20of%20Justice%20that%20the%20United%20States%20Constitution%20forbids%20the%20federal%20indictment%20and%20subsequent%20criminal%20prosecution%20of%20a%20sitting%20President%2C%26quot%3B%20Smith%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BAs%20a%20result%20this%20prosecution%20must%20be%20dismissed%20before%20the%20defendant%20is%20inaugurated.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20a%20separate%20filing%2C%20Smith%20said%20he%20was%20withdrawing%20his%20appeal%20of%20the%20dismissal%20of%20the%20classified%20documents%20case%20against%20Trump%20but%20pursuing%20the%20case%20against%20his%20two%20co-defendants%2C%20Trump%20valet%20Walt%20Nauta%20and%20Mar-a-Lago%20property%20manager%20Carlos%20De%20Oliveira.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3E'Empty%20and%20lawless'%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETrump%2C%20in%20a%20post%20on%20Truth%20Social%2C%20said%20the%20cases%20were%20%26quot%3Bempty%20and%20lawless%2C%20and%20should%20never%20have%20been%20brought.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BOver%20%24100%20Million%20Dollars%20of%20Taxpayer%20Dollars%20has%20been%20wasted%20in%20the%20Democrat%20Party's%20fight%20against%20their%20Political%20Opponent%2C%20ME%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%20%26quot%3BNothing%20like%20this%20has%20ever%20happened%20in%20our%20Country%20before.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETrump%20was%20accused%20of%20conspiracy%20to%20defraud%20the%20United%20States%20and%20conspiracy%20to%20obstruct%20an%20official%20proceeding%20--%20the%20session%20of%20Congress%20called%20to%20certify%20Biden's%20win%2C%20which%20was%20violently%20attacked%20on%20January%206%2C%202021%20by%20a%20mob%20of%20the%20then-president's%20supporters.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETrump%20was%20also%20accused%20of%20seeking%20to%20disenfranchise%20US%20voters%20with%20his%20false%20claims%20that%20he%20won%20the%202020%20election.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20former%20and%20incoming%20president%20also%20faces%20two%20state%20cases%20--%20in%20New%20York%20and%20Georgia.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHe%20was%20convicted%20in%20New%20York%20in%20May%20of%2034%20counts%20of%20falsifying%20business%20records%20to%20cover%20up%20a%20hush%20money%20payment%20to%20porn%20star%20Stormy%20Daniels%20on%20the%20eve%20of%20the%202016%20election%20to%20stop%20her%20from%20revealing%20an%20alleged%202006%20sexual%20encounter.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20Judge%20Juan%20Merchan%20has%20postponed%20sentencing%20while%20he%20considers%20a%20request%20from%20Trump's%20lawyers%20that%20the%20conviction%20be%20thrown%20out%20in%20light%20of%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20ruling%20in%20July%20that%20an%20ex-president%20has%20broad%20immunity%20from%20prosecution.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20Georgia%2C%20Trump%20faces%20racketeering%20charges%20over%20his%20efforts%20to%20subvert%20the%202020%20election%20results%20in%20the%20southern%20state%2C%20but%20that%20case%20will%20likely%20be%20frozen%20while%20he%20is%20in%20office.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ci%3E(Except%20for%20the%20headline%2C%20this%20story%20has%20not%20been%20edited%20by%20NDTV%20staff%20and%20is%20published%20from%20a%20syndicated%20feed.)%3C%2Fi%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1732585800000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2024-11%2For1krfkg_donald-trump-reuters_625x300_06_November_24.jpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fworld-news%2Fjudge-grants-dismissal-of-election-subversion-case-against-trump-7105950%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22A%20judge%20on%20Monday%20granted%20a%20request%20by%20prosecutors%20to%20dismiss%20the%20election%20subversion%20case%20against%20Donald%20Trump%20because%20of%20a%20Justice%20Department%20policy%20of%20not%20prosecuting%20a%20sitting%20president.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fworld-news%2Fjudge-grants-dismissal-of-election-subversion-case-against-trump-7105950%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Macy's%20%24132%20million%20mystery%20has%20auditing%20experts%20scratching%20their%20heads%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221024%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Shoppers%20outside%20Macy's%20Herald%20Square%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F67452b64fa0140cdd5656260%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22683%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EMacy's%20found%20a%20significant%20accounting%20error%20from%20an%20employee.%3Cp%3EMichael%20M.%20Santiago%2FGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3EMacy's%20said%20it%20discovered%20an%20employee%20intentionally%20made%20accounting%20errors%20totaling%20%24132%20to%20%24154%20million.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EAuditing%20experts%20told%20BI%20the%20available%20evidence%20suggests%20a%20failure%20of%20internal%20accounting%20controls.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EThey%20said%20the%20issue%20should%20have%20been%20caught%20much%20earlier%20%E2%80%94regardless%20of%20any%20single%20employee's%20intent.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20accounting%20as%20in%20air%20travel%2C%20a%20common%20saying%20applies%3A%20%26quot%3BIf%20you%20see%20something%2C%20say%20something.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFollowing%20the%20news%20that%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmacys-delays-earnings-investigation-worker-hides-130-million-expenses-2024-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EMacy's%20discovered%20a%20sizable%20error%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20its%20financial%20records%2C%20auditing%20experts%20told%20Business%20Insider%20that%20the%20company%20must%20now%20explain%20how%20its%20controls%20broke%20down.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20retailer%20said%20Monday%20that%20it%20was%20delaying%20its%20quarterly%20earnings%20release%20after%20discovering%20an%20employee%20deliberately%20made%20an%20accounting%20error%20totaling%20between%20%24132%20million%20and%20%24154%20million%20over%20three%20years.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EEven%20in%20a%20situation%20where%20someone%20intentionally%20introduced%20errors%20to%20a%20company's%20books%2C%20former%20KPMG%20partner%20Jerry%20Maginnis%20said%2C%20%26quot%3BYour%20system%20of%20internal%20control%20should%20have%20caught%20it.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESince%20retiring%20from%20the%20accounting%20firm%20in%202015%2C%20Maginnis%20now%20serves%20on%20the%20audit%20committees%20of%20several%20companies%20and%20is%20an%20executive%20in%20residence%20at%20Rowan%20University.%20He%20said%20he%20never%20handled%20financial%20records%20for%20Macy's%2C%20which%20has%20been%20audited%20by%20KPMG%20since%201988.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BSomebody%20else%20should%20have%20been%20reviewing%20and%20catching%20it%2C%20and%20so%20this%20was%20a%20breakdown%20in%20internal%20control%20as%20well%20as%20bad%20accounting%2C%26quot%3B%20Maginnis%20told%20BI.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMacy's%20said%20it%20fired%20an%20individual%20who%20%26quot%3Bintentionally%20made%20erroneous%20accounting%20accrual%20entries%26quot%3B%20and%20launched%20an%20investigation.%20The%20employee%20had%20%26quot%3Bresponsibility%20for%20small%20package%20delivery%20expense%20accounting%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20company%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20retailer%20said%20that%20it%20spent%20%244.36%20billion%20on%20small%20package%20delivery%20expenses%20in%20the%20three%20years%20that%20the%20error%20had%20been%20taking%20place%2C%20making%20the%20error%20less%20than%205%25%20of%20that%20line%20item.%20According%20to%20Macy's%20press%20release%2C%20no%20money%20was%20improperly%20spent.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20employee's%20potential%20motives%20and%20exactly%20what%20went%20wrong%20is%20likely%20to%20be%20the%20subject%20of%20investigation%20by%20Macy's%20audit%20committee%2C%20KPMG%2C%20and%20others%2C%20accounting%20experts%20told%20Business%20Insider.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20last%20time%20Macy's%20reported%20a%20major%20accounting%20issue%20was%20in%202006%20when%20the%20company%20restated%20financials%20over%20a%20%26quot%3Bcash%20flow%20classification%2C%26quot%3B%20according%20to%20Ideagen%20Audit%20Analytics%2C%20a%20research%20and%20data%20provider.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMonday's%20announcement%20preceded%20Macy's%20regularly%20scheduled%20third-quarter%20earnings%20report.%20The%20company%20said%20its%20next%20update%20will%20come%20on%20December%2011.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIf%20they%20weren't%20going%20to%20delay%20their%20earnings%2C%20we%20probably%20never%20would've%20heard%20about%20this%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Michelle%20Leder%2C%20the%20author%20of%20a%20book%20about%20reading%20financial%20statements%20who%20now%20runs%20the%20website%20Footnoted%2C%20which%20analyzes%20securities%20filings.%20%26quot%3BYou%20could%20argue%20that%20maybe%20they've%20already%20disclosed%20more%20than%20they're%20required%20to%20disclose.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWithout%20more%20details%2C%20the%20accounting%20experts%20who%20spoke%20to%20BI%20said%20it%20is%20hard%20to%20understand%20exactly%20what%20happened.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOne%20possible%20explanation%20may%20be%20as%20simple%20as%20%26quot%3Bsometimes%20accountants%20make%20mistakes%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Francine%20McKenna%2C%20a%20former%20accounting%20professional%20who%20now%20publishes%20The%20Dig%20newsletter%20about%20accounting%20topics%20and%20auditing%20firms.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BSometimes%20errors%20accumulate%2C%20and%20then%20what%20happens%20is%20you%20go%20into%20preservation%20mode%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20added.%20%26quot%3BYou%20just%20keep%20perpetuating%20the%20error%20in%20order%20to%20hide%20it%20because%20you%20don't%20want%20to%20raise%20your%20hand%20and%20say%2C%20'An%20error%20happened%2C%20I%20couldn't%20get%20it%20fixed%20for%20a%20year%20and%20a%20half%2C%20and%20now%20the%20number%20is%20really%20big.'%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20stronger%20internal%20controls%20could%20shift%20some%20of%20the%20onus%20off%20of%20individuals%20having%20to%20make%20that%20choice%2C%20Maginnis%20also%20said%20that%20the%20accounting%20profession%20depends%20on%20individuals%20having%20a%20personal%20commitment%20to%20tell%20the%20truth%20at%20all%20times.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ERegulations%20set%20by%20the%20Sarbanes-Oxley%20Act%2C%20which%20require%20public%20companies%20to%20maintain%20effective%20internal%20controls%2C%20are%20intended%20to%20catch%20mistakes%20like%20this%20much%20earlier%20and%20provide%20an%20avenue%20for%20audit%20firms%20to%20issue%20warnings%20about%20company%20controls.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20pressure%20will%20now%20be%20on%20Macy's%20auditor%2C%20KPMG%2C%20to%20show%20that%20it%20is%20appropriately%20scrutinizing%20Macy's%20accounting%20practices%20and%20controls%2C%20McKenna%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20wouldn't%20be%20surprised%20if%20you'll%20see%20a%20material%20weakness%20in%20internal%20controls%20because%20something%20is%20not%20working%20here%2C%26quot%3B%20McKenna%20said.%20%26quot%3BThere%20was%20a%20hole%20somewhere.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cbr%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmacys-earnings-accounting-emloyee-error-raises-control-questions-2024-11%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1732585221000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F67452bbaede4eeae3929814b%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmacys-earnings-accounting-emloyee-error-raises-control-questions-2024-11%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22While%20Macy's%20says%20a%20single%20employee%20was%20responsible%20for%20the%20error%2C%20accounting%20and%20auditing%20experts%20told%20BI%20it%20should%20have%20been%20caught%20much%20earlier.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22dreuter%40businessinsider.com%20(Dominick%20Reuter%2CDakin%20Campbell)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A27%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A